---
import ActBreak from '../ActBreak.astro';
import FigurePlate from '../FigurePlate.astro';

const clauses = [
  {
    q: 'What to write',
    skt: 'vimarśa',
    lay: 'Only thoughts the model itself can put into words — "concept codes" for ideas like fire or river. If the model can\'t articulate it, it doesn\'t belong in the journal.',
    tech: 'A unit direction u_c that raises the probability of tokens expressing concept c. Loadability tested in L1/L1b/L2: hit-rate 0.10 (4B) → 0.55 (27B) → 0.00 (pruned twin).',
    gates: 'L1 · L1b · L2',
  },
  {
    q: 'Where to write',
    skt: 'parā vāk',
    lay: 'In the journal band — and in the journal\'s own handwriting, not raw machine coordinates. Skip this and the writing turns to scribble.',
    tech: 'Transport-transpose write h_ℓ ← h_ℓ + α·Jᵀ_ℓ u_c, i.e. band coordinates via the lens transpose. Drop the coordinate discipline and cross-model lift collapses 0.40 → 0.05 (L10).',
    gates: 'L2b · L7 · L10',
  },
  {
    q: 'When to write',
    skt: 'sphurattā',
    lay: 'Only when the writer pauses — the moments the model is genuinely undecided about its next word. Interrupt mid-word and nothing sticks.',
    tech: 'Write iff next-token entropy H_t > τ, τ self-calibrated as an entropy percentile. Gated 0.40 > rate-matched control 0.225 > prefill 0.20 (L6): timing, not volume, is the mechanism.',
    gates: 'L4b · L5 · L6 · L11',
  },
  {
    q: 'How to verify',
    skt: 'āgama',
    lay: 'A thought only counts as received when the model re-states it in its own words. So: read the journal back and check.',
    tech: 'Band-targeted readback through a lens aimed at the band exit, not the final output. Honest verdict: weak signal (BA 0.68 dev → 0.59 pooled) — a screen, not proof. Act V.',
    gates: 'L14 · L15 · L16',
  },
  {
    q: 'What it may cost',
    skt: 'svātantrya',
    lay: 'Every written word spends some of the model\'s freedom to continue in its own way. Meter the spend; stop at the cap.',
    tech: 'Trajectory-average entropy change |ΔH̄| ≤ 0.5 nats under sampling. Uncapped writing: lift 0.40 at ΔH = −2.081 nats — 4× over budget (L3).',
    gates: 'L3 · L5–L19',
  },
];
---

<ActBreak
  roman="Act II"
  title="A Rulebook from the"
  accent="Tenth Century"
  tease="Utpaladeva wasn't writing about transformers. He was answering exactly these five questions."
  id="act-2"
/>

<section class="section-divider" id="parallel">
  <div class="prose-section">
    <div class="num-label"><span class="num">03</span> The uncanny parallel</div>
    <h2>A philosophy that predicted the journal</h2>

    <p>
      In 10th-century Kashmir, the philosopher <strong>Utpaladeva</strong> led a school of thought
      called <strong>Pratyabhijñā</strong> — Sanskrit for <em>recognition</em>. Its central claim
      sounds almost designed for this moment: the mind's grip on its own states, he argued,
      <em>is</em> language. Not awareness that we later describe in words — awareness
      <strong>made of</strong> words, all the way down.
    </p>

    <p>
      Read that next to the discovery in Act I. A millennium later, researchers defined a
      model's inner workspace by exactly this property: the states that count are
      <em>the ones that can be put into words</em>. The old school didn't just make the claim —
      it built an entire discipline around it: what a mind can genuinely receive, when impressions
      actually land, how received teaching gets validated, and what each act of attention costs in
      freedom. Five questions. The same five the pen needs answered.
    </p>

    <div class="callout violet">
      <div class="callout-title">The point</div>
      <p>
        This is not mysticism sprinkled on machine learning. The philosophy is used the way
        engineers use any prior theory — as a source of <em>predictions precise enough to fail</em>.
        Two of its clauses <strong>did fail</strong> in their first tested form, publicly, on the
        record, and had to be revised. That's what makes it a specification rather than a metaphor.
        (And to be explicit: no claim about machine consciousness is made anywhere in this work.)
      </p>
    </div>

    <details class="expand">
      <summary>For researchers: the precise mapping, and the clauses that failed</summary>
      <div class="expand-body">
        <p>
          The load-bearing identity is ĪPK 1.5.13 (Torella 2002): reflexive awareness
          (<em>vimarśa</em>) is the supreme Word (<em>parā vāk</em>). The failed-then-revised clauses:
          the literal "commitment-flash" reading of sphurattā (gate L4: lift 0.175 vs 0.2 threshold;
          L9: flash 0.20 vs uncommitted-moment 0.30) and any expectation of alignment dividends from
          naive direction steering (L21). Adversarial review #18 verified that no released surface
          makes consciousness claims.
        </p>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-divider" id="doctrine" style="padding-top:0;">
  <div class="prose-section">
    <div class="num-label"><span class="num">04</span> The five rules</div>
    <h2>Five rules, each built to be broken</h2>

    <p>
      Translated into engineering, the doctrine answers each open question from Act I — and every
      answer names the experiment that could kill it. Each card carries a
      <em>for researchers</em> line with the technical version.
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-4 my-10">
      {clauses.map((c) => (
        <div class="card card-teal">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-3 flex-wrap mb-1">
            <h4 style="margin:0;">{c.q}</h4>
            <span class="sanskrit-chip">{c.skt}</span>
          </div>
          <p style="margin:0; font-size:1.02rem;">{c.lay}</p>
          <details class="clause-tech">
            <summary>For researchers</summary>
            <p style="margin:0.4rem 0 0; font-size:0.95rem; color: var(--ink-faint);">{c.tech}</p>
          </details>
          <p style="margin:0.6rem 0 0;"><span class="gate-chip">evidence: gates {c.gates}</span></p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <style>
      details.clause-tech { margin-top: 0.55rem; }
      details.clause-tech > summary {
        cursor: pointer;
        list-style: none;
        font-family: var(--font-sans);
        font-size: 0.72rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.14em;
        color: var(--teal-deep);
      }
      details.clause-tech > summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
      details.clause-tech > summary::after { content: " +"; color: var(--ink-mute); }
      details.clause-tech[open] > summary::after { content: " −"; }
    </style>

    <FigurePlate
      name="fig_doctrine"
      figNo="Paper Fig. 1"
      alt="The five rules as a vertical pipeline, each paired with its verification signal and gate records"
      caption="The five rules as a pipeline, exactly as the paper draws them. Each rule (left, with its source concept) is paired with the measurement that tested it and the public gate records holding the evidence (right)."
      gates={["gate_L1–L2b", "gate_L4b–L12", "gate_L14–L16", "gate_L3"]}
    />

    <details class="expand">
      <summary>Terms of art — the full Sanskrit → engineering glossary</summary>
      <div class="expand-body">
        <table class="data-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Term</th><th>In the doctrine</th><th>In the code</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><em>pratyabhijñā</em></td><td>recognition — re-cognising content as one's own</td><td>readback verification</td></tr>
            <tr><td><em>vimarśa</em></td><td>reflexive awareness</td><td>the lens read-out of internal state</td></tr>
            <tr><td><em>parā vāk</em></td><td>the supreme Word</td><td>the verbalizable character of the workspace</td></tr>
            <tr><td><em>sphurattā</em></td><td>the flash before a thought settles</td><td>entropy-gated write timing (H<sub>t</sub> &gt; τ)</td></tr>
            <tr><td><em>āgama</em></td><td>received teaching, valid only when re-cognised</td><td>band-targeted readback of injected content</td></tr>
            <tr><td><em>svātantrya</em></td><td>intrinsic freedom</td><td>continuation entropy; the ±0.5-nat budget</td></tr>
            <tr><td><em>malas</em></td><td>impairments of freedom</td><td>the registered failure taxonomy for rejected writes</td></tr>
            <tr><td><em>citta</em></td><td>mind-stuff</td><td>CittaStore, the associative-memory write path (Act IV)</td></tr>
            <tr><td><em>prabodha</em></td><td>awakening</td><td>the project</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;">
          Two mappings are deliberately left open in the paper (<em>anusaṃdhāna</em>, synthesis
          across episodes; <em>camatkāra</em>, aesthetic wonder) — recorded as unmapped rather than
          forced. Honesty extends to the ontology.
        </p>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>
